title: Final exams of my college undergrad degree and I feel so many emotions
content: I have to start studying for my final exams of my undergrad college and there are so many emotions swirling and I don’t know what to do. I have no motivation to study for them, I already passed these classes but I know I should and I will. I am terrified cause especially one of these exams is in the hardest class I’ve ever taken and even though I passed mathematically it still scares me for some reason. I feel relief that it’s almost over, but I’m depressed that it’s not over yet. Overall just kinda unsure how to manage all these emotions.

title: It's never too late
content: There's a famous Japanese proverb that says, "if you find yourself on the wrong train, get off at the next station." It doesn't matter if you have to pay a high cost for a new ticket. It doesn't matter if you're embarrassed to have made a mistake. Every price you pay to fix the situation is worth not going the wrong way, and starting to go the right way. Not having the courage to get off means going to the wrong destination. This, of course, isn't about trains. It's about life.
